{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1783160705,"nonce":"m/Yc+8J3cJ8JrjCWAjLsDcuPArQ=","message":"Fixed in PR #76 (squash c15f74a). The actual bug: a `///` doc comment desugars to `#[doc = \"...\"]`, and the hand-rolled field-attribute parser (table.rs::apply_attribute, shared by Table/View/CTE) rejected any attribute it did not recognize, so documenting a field of a derived struct was a hard compile error (`unsupported Table field attribute doc`). Fix: a shared `common::is_ignored_attribute` helper; skip `doc` in apply_attribute (Table/View/CTE) and in common::struct_fields (Schema/Database). ColumnType already skipped foreign attributes. Doc comments now compile and stay on the original items. New regression test crates/squealy/tests/doc_comments.rs derives Table/View/Schema/Database/ColumnType all carrying /// docs on structs + fields (fails to build on the pre-fix main). CI green, Codex clean first pass. NOTE: scoped to the parser fix only — populating the model comment fields / rendering COMMENT ON (the DACFx feature described in the original issue text) was explicitly out of scope and not done here.","files":null}]}